WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:15.833 --> 00:00:17.073
<i>In the beginning.</i>

3
00:00:17.541 --> 00:00:21.333
<i>before the Six Singularities
and the dawn of creation.</i>

4
00:00:21.833 --> 00:00:23.875
<i>came the Celestials.</i>

5
00:00:30.125 --> 00:00:35.790
Now. with the power of the Eternal
Guardians flowing through me.

6
00:00:35.791 --> 00:00:41.791
let the power of creation
bring forth my rebirth!

7
00:00:46.958 --> 00:00:49.249
My rebirth! My rebirth!

8
00:00:49.250 --> 00:00:51.707
Okay. well. that's
not working. Howard?

9
00:00:51.708 --> 00:00:53.415
And cut!

10
00:00:53.416 --> 00:00:55.875
Okay. let's reset. We'll
do it one more time.

11
00:00:56.583 --> 00:01:00.165
<i>In this universe. Agatha
Harkness' quest for power led her</i>

12
00:01:00.166 --> 00:01:03.500
<i>to discover the Celestial
growing deep within the Earth.</i>

13
00:01:04.375 --> 00:01:06.790
<i>Looking to take its
cosmic energy for herself.</i>

14
00:01:06.791 --> 00:01:10.041
<i>she set out to design a
spell to siphon its power.</i>

15
00:01:10.583 --> 00:01:15.500
<i>But pulling off a ritual of that scale
would require an equally big production.</i>

16
00:01:16.125 --> 00:01:19.749
<i>So. she turned to a blossoming
industry that had built its reputation</i>

17
00:01:19.750 --> 00:01:23.291
<i>financing the big dreams
of even bigger egos.</i>

18
00:01:23.875 --> 00:01:24.874
<i>Hollywood.</i>

19
00:01:24.875 --> 00:01:28.499
<i>Where upstart mogul. Howard
Stark. was happy to foot the bill.</i>

20
00:01:28.500 --> 00:01:32.290
Agatha. darling. those in-camera effects.
I still don't know how you do it!

21
00:01:32.291 --> 00:01:34.290
Just a little bit
of "movie magic."

22
00:01:34.291 --> 00:01:37.290
But it's not working. This
spell is just not working!

23
00:01:37.291 --> 00:01:40.374
In the scene. that is. We
may need to. uh. re-stage.

24
00:01:40.375 --> 00:01:42.832
Fantastic! That's
lunch. everyone.

25
00:01:42.833 --> 00:01:45.208
Now. where's my
AD? Jarvis? Jarvis!

26
00:01:45.708 --> 00:01:47.790
Don't tell me. Not
more new pages.

27
00:01:47.791 --> 00:01:50.790
We have already re-shot the
Third Act set piece five times.

28
00:01:50.791 --> 00:01:53.124
And we'll shoot it a hundred
more. if that's what it takes!

29
00:01:53.125 --> 00:01:55.707
To add what? Another
mind-numbing action spectacle?

30
00:01:55.708 --> 00:01:58.332
Big fights? Bigger explosions?
I think we've seen it.

31
00:01:58.333 --> 00:01:59.790
- You know. you're right.
- I am?

32
00:01:59.791 --> 00:02:01.582
- He is?
- We need to expand this picture

33
00:02:01.583 --> 00:02:03.082
to give it that
oomph I'm missing.

34
00:02:03.083 --> 00:02:05.082
We need more star power.

35
00:02:05.083 --> 00:02:07.165
- A co-star!
- How can I steal the show

36
00:02:07.166 --> 00:02:08.749
when there's no one
to steal it from.

37
00:02:08.750 --> 00:02:11.540
Of course! The Capulets had the
Montagues. The Hatfields. the McCoys.

38
00:02:11.541 --> 00:02:13.624
My auntie had the recluse
in the apartment upstairs.

39
00:02:13.625 --> 00:02:15.582
You need a foil! A perfectly
placed grain of salt

40
00:02:15.583 --> 00:02:17.624
to complement the seasonings
simmering in the pan!

41
00:02:17.625 --> 00:02:19.249
Anything but more actors.

42
00:02:19.250 --> 00:02:22.665
I can see it now. Our Cosmic Queen is
sitting on a hand no one else can beat.

43
00:02:22.666 --> 00:02:25.499
That is. until a mysterious
new player blows into town.

44
00:02:25.500 --> 00:02:26.790
hot on her lofty ambitions.

45
00:02:26.791 --> 00:02:29.290
Yes. yes. Do they fight?
Do they fall in love?

46
00:02:29.291 --> 00:02:33.207
No. they'll dance. With dozens
of backup dancers on each side.

47
00:02:33.208 --> 00:02:36.707
And we'll lift the lighting rig so
the sets can be three times as tall.

48
00:02:36.708 --> 00:02:38.165
- Yes!
- Wait. No. No. no.

49
00:02:38.166 --> 00:02:40.249
Jarvis! It's about time you
caught the creative bug.

50
00:02:40.250 --> 00:02:41.624
- I wasn't...
- That is just genius.

51
00:02:41.625 --> 00:02:43.040
- It's a disaster.
- Who we thinking?

52
00:02:43.041 --> 00:02:45.207
Bogie? Gable? Cary Grant
does owe me a favor.

53
00:02:45.208 --> 00:02:49.000
No. no. there's only one actor on
Earth who can complete our picture.

54
00:02:49.500 --> 00:02:51.708
I thought I could do it
without him. but now I see.

55
00:02:52.291 --> 00:02:53.291
I need him.

56
00:02:53.916 --> 00:02:54.916
Kingo.

57
00:03:01.875 --> 00:03:02.916
<i>Time.</i>

58
00:03:06.375 --> 00:03:07.458
<i>Space.</i>

59
00:03:09.208 --> 00:03:10.250
<i>Reality.</i>

60
00:03:13.125 --> 00:03:14.791
<i>It's more than a linear path.</i>

61
00:03:19.666 --> 00:03:24.166
<i>It's a prism of
endless possibility.</i>

62
00:03:26.708 --> 00:03:30.125
<i>Where a single choice can branch
out into infinite realities.</i>

63
00:03:32.916 --> 00:03:35.666
<i>creating alternate worlds
from the ones you know.</i>

64
00:03:39.791 --> 00:03:41.125
<i>I am the Watcher.</i>

65
00:03:43.375 --> 00:03:46.541
<i>I am your guide through
these vast new realities.</i>

66
00:03:47.958 --> 00:03:51.458
<i>Follow me and ponder
the question...</i>

67
00:03:55.125 --> 00:03:56.750
<i>"What if?"</i>

68
00:04:27.041 --> 00:04:28.041
Mr. Kingo.

69
00:04:28.583 --> 00:04:31.749
I'm Edwin Jarvis. Mr. Stark's
personal butler and second AD.

70
00:04:31.750 --> 00:04:33.624
Welcome to Stark Pictures.

71
00:04:33.625 --> 00:04:34.915
Wow!

72
00:04:34.916 --> 00:04:37.415
And I thought we did things
over-the-top in Bollywood.

73
00:04:37.416 --> 00:04:40.790
I've always been partial to
the axiom that "less is more."

74
00:04:40.791 --> 00:04:42.165
But for Mr. Stark...

75
00:04:42.166 --> 00:04:43.624
More is just the opening offer.

76
00:04:43.625 --> 00:04:45.457
Kingo. it's an honor
to have you onboard.

77
00:04:45.458 --> 00:04:48.040
Now. this number we've put together
is off the charts. Literally.

78
00:04:48.041 --> 00:04:50.707
I've got enough dancers in there
to light up a Richter scale.

79
00:04:50.708 --> 00:04:52.582
You ready to cross steps
with our leading lady?

80
00:04:52.583 --> 00:04:56.040
Howard. something tells me this
is a part I was born to play.

81
00:04:56.041 --> 00:04:58.332
The lights
are hot. cameras loaded.

82
00:04:58.333 --> 00:05:00.249
and safeties removed from
all our pyrotechnics!

83
00:05:00.250 --> 00:05:01.332
What? I'm sorry. what?

84
00:05:01.333 --> 00:05:02.665
Is there anything else you need?

85
00:05:02.666 --> 00:05:04.915
- I'm more than ready.
- What about the choreography?

86
00:05:04.916 --> 00:05:07.332
- Was it up to snuff?
- Yes. The moves are great.

87
00:05:07.333 --> 00:05:10.040
but I assume there's room
for a little improvisation?

88
00:05:10.041 --> 00:05:12.749
Absolutely! Absolutely! Kingo.
I'll be honest with you.

89
00:05:12.750 --> 00:05:15.082
This one's gonna be a
doozy. A real barn burner.

90
00:05:15.083 --> 00:05:17.124
The biggest scene ever
captured on celluloid.

91
00:05:17.125 --> 00:05:18.332
Don't worry. Howard.

92
00:05:18.333 --> 00:05:21.833
I've been preparing for our
showdown for quite some time.

93
00:05:23.416 --> 00:05:27.040
Okay. people! This is it.
Our big musical number.

94
00:05:27.041 --> 00:05:29.457
I want glitz. I want glamour.

95
00:05:29.458 --> 00:05:31.458
I want emotion!
I want commotion!

96
00:05:32.041 --> 00:05:34.375
I want you to wow me
with your razzle-dazzle.

97
00:05:35.083 --> 00:05:38.874
I want Busby Berkeley to see this
and contemplate becoming a realtor!

98
00:05:38.875 --> 00:05:40.415
Quiet on set!

99
00:05:40.416 --> 00:05:41.816
Lights!

100
00:05:42.708 --> 00:05:43.791
Camera!

101
00:05:45.666 --> 00:05:46.666
TR 62. take one.

102
00:05:47.666 --> 00:05:49.291
And...

103
00:05:50.083 --> 00:05:51.082
action!

104
00:06:33.333 --> 00:06:37.457
The challenge has been made. Will
our Cosmic Queen heed the call?

105
00:06:37.458 --> 00:06:39.583
Move in. Camera A.

106
00:06:51.333 --> 00:06:52.708
She answers!

107
00:06:53.291 --> 00:06:54.916
There she is.

108
00:06:55.916 --> 00:06:57.374
There he is.

109
00:06:57.375 --> 00:06:58.707
It's all led up to this.

110
00:06:58.708 --> 00:07:01.415
The final Eternal champion
arrives at the zero hour.

111
00:07:01.416 --> 00:07:04.582
in a last. desperate bid to
stay the queen's cosmic hand!

112
00:07:51.666 --> 00:07:54.624
Will she defeat
him? Will he defeat her?

113
00:07:54.625 --> 00:07:56.000
Will they dance?

114
00:07:58.208 --> 00:07:59.583
They will!

115
00:08:01.708 --> 00:08:04.500
You're the missing piece I've
been waiting lifetimes for.

116
00:08:06.875 --> 00:08:09.874
Oh. I know. But I'm here
to put your vanity project

117
00:08:09.875 --> 00:08:11.208
into turnaround.

118
00:08:14.625 --> 00:08:16.790
So. you "know" know.

119
00:08:16.791 --> 00:08:18.415
And you still had the
stones to show up.

120
00:08:18.416 --> 00:08:19.958
Someone needs to stop you.

121
00:08:21.875 --> 00:08:24.290
Oh. honey. I'm just out
here making blockbusters.

122
00:08:24.291 --> 00:08:27.166
You and the Eternals are the
ones who wanna destroy the world.

123
00:08:30.083 --> 00:08:32.666
You have no idea what
forces you're meddling with.

124
00:08:33.166 --> 00:08:34.208
Right back at ya.

125
00:08:41.916 --> 00:08:43.915
A little advice. one
hoofer to another.

126
00:08:43.916 --> 00:08:45.583
In this town?

127
00:08:46.583 --> 00:08:48.791
Never mess with Number
One on the Call Sheet.

128
00:08:52.916 --> 00:08:54.708
Okay. Kingo. Make
this look good!

129
00:08:58.791 --> 00:09:00.333
Hot dog! That was
out of this world!

130
00:09:13.666 --> 00:09:16.082
Okay. Show's over.

131
00:09:16.083 --> 00:09:17.750
Time to break out the big guns.

132
00:09:20.333 --> 00:09:21.457
Oh. that's not in the script.

133
00:09:21.458 --> 00:09:23.207
Is that in the script?
Are these blue pages?

134
00:09:23.208 --> 00:09:25.125
Shush. Jarvis! It's
great! Keep shooting!

135
00:09:27.083 --> 00:09:30.499
Uh. I'm sorry. Your powers
are "finger pistols"?

136
00:09:30.500 --> 00:09:31.999
Okay. No.

137
00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:34.332
I fire energy. Projections.

138
00:09:34.333 --> 00:09:37.375
Ah. right. From your
fingers. Pew! Pew!

139
00:09:39.791 --> 00:09:42.124
Okay. No... Stop with
your hands. Stop!

140
00:09:42.125 --> 00:09:44.332
Listen. these powers are cool.

141
00:09:44.333 --> 00:09:46.958
A lot of people think
these powers are very cool.

142
00:09:49.750 --> 00:09:52.082
What? Those powers are Thena's!

143
00:09:52.083 --> 00:09:54.499
And Makkari's and Gilgamesh's
and everyone else's.

144
00:09:56.791 --> 00:09:58.833
- Oh!
- Yes!

145
00:10:00.750 --> 00:10:01.750
Ah!

146
00:10:05.666 --> 00:10:06.666
Yes!

147
00:10:07.791 --> 00:10:08.791
Ow!

148
00:10:09.791 --> 00:10:10.790
Whoa!

149
00:10:10.791 --> 00:10:11.875
Oh!

150
00:10:33.333 --> 00:10:34.874
And... cut!

151
00:10:36.125 --> 00:10:39.040
Wowza! That chemistry was
hotter than the Hindenburg!

152
00:10:39.041 --> 00:10:41.249
I really believed you two
wanted to kill each other.

153
00:10:41.250 --> 00:10:43.166
Oh! No. no.
no. We're just acting.

154
00:10:43.666 --> 00:10:45.290
Totally just acting.

155
00:10:45.291 --> 00:10:48.582
Both of us just acting
so hard right now.

156
00:10:48.583 --> 00:10:51.833
Oh. really? I'd say one of us
is acting really bad right now.

157
00:10:52.708 --> 00:10:56.040
This calls for a celebration!
After-party! My place!

158
00:10:56.041 --> 00:10:57.832
- Jarvis. give 'em the deets.
- Fine.

159
00:10:57.833 --> 00:11:00.290
Top of the hill. everybody. Just
above the Hollywoodland sign.

160
00:11:00.291 --> 00:11:03.333
It's the house that will make you
question the decency of capitalism.

161
00:11:09.833 --> 00:11:11.957
If you mean to kill
me. be forewarned.

162
00:11:11.958 --> 00:11:14.790
I know several heart-wrenching.
dying monologues.

163
00:11:14.791 --> 00:11:16.415
and I will regale you with them.

164
00:11:16.416 --> 00:11:19.874
Oh. Kingo. You've pegged me as
the villain of this picture.

165
00:11:19.875 --> 00:11:21.124
but you've got it all wrong.

166
00:11:21.125 --> 00:11:22.290
I'm the hero.

167
00:11:22.291 --> 00:11:24.874
You killed my friends.
stole their powers.

168
00:11:24.875 --> 00:11:29.374
Relax. I didn't kill anyone.
I "borrowed" their powers.

169
00:11:29.375 --> 00:11:32.915
I assure you. your friends are
all safe and sound in storage.

170
00:11:32.916 --> 00:11:36.165
The backlot has a creature shop.
They blend right in.

171
00:11:36.166 --> 00:11:38.290
Agatha. release them.

172
00:11:38.291 --> 00:11:41.583
Swear on the Oscar I
plan to win. I will.

173
00:11:42.083 --> 00:11:44.040
Once I have saved my world

174
00:11:44.041 --> 00:11:48.083
from that Third Act surprise you've
got brewing in the center of the Earth.

175
00:11:48.583 --> 00:11:49.582
But...

176
00:11:49.583 --> 00:11:51.540
And this
is the hard part.

177
00:11:51.541 --> 00:11:54.000
I can't do it
without you. Kingo.

178
00:11:55.166 --> 00:11:59.500
I need your energy to complete my spell.
to save everything I know and love.

179
00:12:00.500 --> 00:12:02.165
Arishem made me the
new Prime Eternal.

180
00:12:02.166 --> 00:12:03.790
I need to protect Tiamut

181
00:12:03.791 --> 00:12:06.332
and the billions of lives
his Emergence will create.

182
00:12:06.333 --> 00:12:08.665
Sorry. scout. but I
can see you reaching.

183
00:12:08.666 --> 00:12:10.790
There's no way
Arishem won you over

184
00:12:10.791 --> 00:12:14.832
with some golden ball and top
billing on a doomed planet.

185
00:12:14.833 --> 00:12:16.582
You aren't like
the other Eternals.

186
00:12:16.583 --> 00:12:17.957
And what makes you say that?

187
00:12:17.958 --> 00:12:21.499
Because you haven't just
lived among humanity.

188
00:12:21.500 --> 00:12:23.625
you have lived as them.

189
00:12:24.041 --> 00:12:25.165
Oh!

190
00:12:25.166 --> 00:12:29.790
Seeing the beauty.
telling their stories

191
00:12:29.791 --> 00:12:34.333
showing them who they really
are as only an actor can.

192
00:12:34.833 --> 00:12:36.207
Oh. that is true.

193
00:12:36.208 --> 00:12:39.166
Acting is the most noble
profession on Earth.

194
00:12:39.666 --> 00:12:42.457
But do you really expect
me to betray Arishem?

195
00:12:42.458 --> 00:12:45.915
Forsake a mission I've
dedicated eons to?

196
00:12:45.916 --> 00:12:47.165
Never going to happen.

197
00:12:47.166 --> 00:12:48.874
- Never.
- I can get Howard to offer you

198
00:12:48.875 --> 00:12:50.582
- a three-picture deal.
- Okay. I'll do it.

199
00:12:50.583 --> 00:12:52.415
Oh. I guess I should've
led with that.

200
00:12:52.416 --> 00:12:54.790
But I'm gonna need full
green light approval.

201
00:12:54.791 --> 00:12:56.207
and my own shingle on the lot.

202
00:12:56.208 --> 00:13:00.165
Ooh. Plus. I've been looking to
transition into indulgent. art house fair.

203
00:13:00.166 --> 00:13:01.374
You know. no plot.

204
00:13:01.375 --> 00:13:04.041
Abrupt. arbitrary cuts. Cut!

205
00:13:06.000 --> 00:13:08.875
Me staring into camera with
no expression on my face.

206
00:13:10.625 --> 00:13:12.957
That last one sounds
like a nightmare.

207
00:13:12.958 --> 00:13:17.124
But for the literal sake of the
world. I guess I'll allow it.

208
00:13:17.125 --> 00:13:19.000
And you have to bring
back my friends.

209
00:13:19.708 --> 00:13:22.624
Very well. Let's get
this show on the road.

210
00:13:28.875 --> 00:13:32.499
Did you think I
would not see your failure?

211
00:13:32.500 --> 00:13:34.582
You have chosen your side.

212
00:13:34.583 --> 00:13:37.791
And now. you will die on it.

213
00:13:41.458 --> 00:13:43.290
Arishem is coming.

214
00:13:43.291 --> 00:13:45.916
It would take the power of
another Celestial to stop him.

215
00:13:46.500 --> 00:13:47.874
Another Celestial.

216
00:13:49.166 --> 00:13:50.875
Fasten your seat belt. honey.

217
00:13:51.458 --> 00:13:53.250
It's time for my makeover.

218
00:13:59.541 --> 00:14:02.165
Jarvis. this night's
shaping up to be an instant classic.

219
00:14:02.166 --> 00:14:05.165
Yes. I suppose if the relevant
metric is "property damage."

220
00:14:05.166 --> 00:14:07.915
Howard! Hi. You're still
conscious. Can we chat?

221
00:14:07.916 --> 00:14:09.832
Aggie! Kingo! About time!

222
00:14:09.833 --> 00:14:10.999
Jarvis. bust out the grappa!

223
00:14:11.000 --> 00:14:12.957
Sorry. Howard. No
time for digestifs.

224
00:14:12.958 --> 00:14:14.499
Still. maybe pour
it anyway. though.

225
00:14:14.500 --> 00:14:16.499
We had a bout of
creative inspiration.

226
00:14:16.500 --> 00:14:18.749
Is that some kinda euphemism?
Are you two a thing now?

227
00:14:18.750 --> 00:14:20.430
- Sorry. Not my type.
- Sorry. Not my type.

228
00:14:20.875 --> 00:14:22.749
But we do have chemistry.

229
00:14:22.750 --> 00:14:25.499
And with Kingo's help. we've finally
cracked the Third Act set piece.

230
00:14:25.500 --> 00:14:27.457
Amazing! I'll check out
the pages first thing...

231
00:14:27.458 --> 00:14:29.790
No. no. no. We can't risk
sitting on these creative juices.

232
00:14:29.791 --> 00:14:31.165
We gotta shoot this finale...

233
00:14:31.166 --> 00:14:32.249
- Now!
- Right now!

234
00:14:32.250 --> 00:14:34.999
Impossible. When Ms. Harkness
opted to rewrite the Third Act.

235
00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:38.374
for the sixth time. I might
add. we broke down the sets.

236
00:14:38.375 --> 00:14:40.207
"Broke down the..." What
are you talking about?

237
00:14:40.208 --> 00:14:41.290
Ugh. damn it!

238
00:14:41.291 --> 00:14:44.707
You've no idea how many runes I
had to paint by hand on those sets.

239
00:14:44.708 --> 00:14:46.124
Come on. Think. think. think.

240
00:14:46.125 --> 00:14:50.624
There's gotta be a cursed swamp. a
haunted house. something we can use.

241
00:14:50.625 --> 00:14:53.040
Bingo. baby!
Griffith Observatory.

242
00:14:53.041 --> 00:14:54.999
It should be big enough
for all the runes.

243
00:14:55.000 --> 00:14:56.582
We can shoot the finale there!

244
00:14:56.583 --> 00:14:59.874
And with what dark magic do you expect
me to pull permits at this hour?

245
00:14:59.875 --> 00:15:02.165
For that kind of production
value. I'll buy the joint.

246
00:15:02.166 --> 00:15:04.999
Load up the limo. Jarvis!
We're doin' a company move!

247
00:15:05.000 --> 00:15:06.583
Actually. let's take our ride.

248
00:15:09.541 --> 00:15:10.625
Oh. my...

249
00:15:12.708 --> 00:15:13.791
An alien spaceship.

250
00:15:14.291 --> 00:15:16.707
I gotta hand it to you.
Aggie. You had me fooled.

251
00:15:16.708 --> 00:15:18.124
- I thought you were a witch.
- Yes.

252
00:15:18.125 --> 00:15:19.832
- But he's the space alien.
- Wait. What?

253
00:15:19.833 --> 00:15:21.707
Technically. I'm more
of a space robot.

254
00:15:21.708 --> 00:15:23.249
You are?

255
00:15:23.250 --> 00:15:24.790
Howard. you knew?

256
00:15:24.791 --> 00:15:25.915
You knew?

257
00:15:25.916 --> 00:15:26.999
I'm Howard Stark!

258
00:15:27.000 --> 00:15:29.082
I'm the smartest person on
Earth. Of course. I knew.

259
00:15:29.083 --> 00:15:30.957
I also knew I'd save a
hell of a lot of money

260
00:15:30.958 --> 00:15:32.957
on special effects
using actual magic.

261
00:15:32.958 --> 00:15:36.749
Look. everyone in this town has a
secret. It's what makes it interesting.

262
00:15:36.750 --> 00:15:40.749
So. whatever's about to go down. I'm
here for you. Just let me film it.

263
00:15:40.750 --> 00:15:43.374
But once we save the day. I
want a look under your hood.

264
00:15:43.375 --> 00:15:46.125
I am sensing major
patent potential.

265
00:15:46.875 --> 00:15:48.125
Okay. y'all. Let's do it.

266
00:16:05.541 --> 00:16:07.874
Okay. We've got five cameras
set up for maximum coverage.

267
00:16:07.875 --> 00:16:09.957
"A" Camera's gonna
be trained on Agatha.

268
00:16:09.958 --> 00:16:14.500
Um. I think you're gonna wanna swap
out the lens for something... wider.

269
00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:17.999
Jarvis!

270
00:16:18.000 --> 00:16:20.249
Jarvis.
Jarvis. please.

271
00:16:20.250 --> 00:16:22.332
The line needs to
be more confident.

272
00:16:22.333 --> 00:16:25.832
This also needs a little touch-up.
okay? Lean into the room's energy.

273
00:16:25.833 --> 00:16:27.374
If you'll forgive
me. Ms. Harkness.

274
00:16:27.375 --> 00:16:30.332
We didn't do a lot of occult
rituals when I trained at Balmoral.

275
00:16:30.333 --> 00:16:32.749
Hey. sassy. I suggested we
bring in the set dec team.

276
00:16:32.750 --> 00:16:34.582
but you said we couldn't
afford the overages.

277
00:16:34.583 --> 00:16:36.332
So. now we're here
with your lame energy.

278
00:16:36.333 --> 00:16:37.416
Aggie?

279
00:16:39.458 --> 00:16:41.083
Is that part of the opening act?

280
00:16:43.916 --> 00:16:44.999
Arishem.

281
00:16:45.000 --> 00:16:48.125
Okay. Then. places.
people! It's showtime.

282
00:17:02.625 --> 00:17:05.999
Not gonna lie. getting some
ritual sacrifice vibes here.

283
00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:08.457
You look great. Chin
up! Chin up! That's it.

284
00:17:08.458 --> 00:17:10.665
And start making
space for that Oscar.

285
00:17:10.666 --> 00:17:15.165
From the stars in the sky
to the depths of the Earth.

286
00:17:15.166 --> 00:17:21.166
Let the power of creation
bring forth my rebirth!

287
00:17:40.250 --> 00:17:43.165
Finally. your
power will be mine!

288
00:18:14.083 --> 00:18:16.082
Should we be concerned?

289
00:18:16.083 --> 00:18:18.125
We'll be legends!

290
00:19:02.333 --> 00:19:04.999
Oh. she is beautiful.

291
00:19:05.000 --> 00:19:06.249
Are you getting this?

292
00:19:06.250 --> 00:19:09.166
This is the greatest
footage ever shot!

293
00:19:13.833 --> 00:19:15.250
This is gold!

294
00:19:17.666 --> 00:19:22.000
This power. it's... everything.

295
00:19:39.166 --> 00:19:41.916
It's him. He's here.

296
00:19:43.583 --> 00:19:45.582
It must feel strange

297
00:19:45.583 --> 00:19:47.749
for such a primitive being

298
00:19:47.750 --> 00:19:51.415
to suddenly possess
a power so cosmic.

299
00:19:51.416 --> 00:19:56.332
Oh. honey. cosmic is just my size.
Haven't you seen the marquee?

300
00:19:56.333 --> 00:19:57.665
I'm a star.

301
00:19:57.666 --> 00:20:01.582
You are a heretic.
Agatha Harkness.

302
00:20:01.583 --> 00:20:04.457
And you will be judged as such.

303
00:20:04.458 --> 00:20:06.125
Oh. yeah? Judge this. Boom!

304
00:20:10.583 --> 00:20:13.665
Oh. boy! Cecil B. DeMille's gonna
be pissed when he sees this footage.

305
00:20:13.666 --> 00:20:14.749
Film it! Film it!

306
00:20:14.750 --> 00:20:17.040
I'm filming it! I'm
filming it! I'm filming it!

307
00:20:17.041 --> 00:20:20.625
Howard. something tells me she's
got the whole world watching.

308
00:20:26.750 --> 00:20:27.749
Hah!

309
00:20:29.041 --> 00:20:30.290
Yes!

310
00:20:30.291 --> 00:20:32.832
Your vanity blinds you.

311
00:20:38.833 --> 00:20:40.375
- Oh!
- No!

312
00:20:40.916 --> 00:20:43.249
A Celestial creates life.

313
00:20:43.250 --> 00:20:46.666
It does not glorify
its own existence.

314
00:20:55.958 --> 00:20:57.707
When will you see?

315
00:20:57.708 --> 00:21:01.915
You will always be too
human to wield such power.

316
00:21:01.916 --> 00:21:04.415
Oh. that's cute.
You think I missed?

317
00:21:04.416 --> 00:21:07.583
Truth is. I was just getting
you to hit your mark.

318
00:21:16.416 --> 00:21:18.540
What? How did you?

319
00:21:18.541 --> 00:21:20.749
It's called acting. love.

320
00:21:20.750 --> 00:21:24.458
And I'm afraid you are the next
character I'm gonna become.

321
00:21:43.125 --> 00:21:45.707
Humdinger. That's a showstopper.

322
00:21:45.708 --> 00:21:47.999
Eddie. tell me
you were in focus.

323
00:21:48.000 --> 00:21:49.665
Yes. I think we've got it.

324
00:21:49.666 --> 00:21:51.124
The angles!

325
00:21:51.125 --> 00:21:53.290
Performance of a
lifetime. Agatha.

326
00:21:53.291 --> 00:21:54.874
I think that's a wrap.

327
00:21:54.875 --> 00:21:58.249
Oh. Kingo. The
show's not over yet.

328
00:21:58.250 --> 00:22:00.290
Agatha. what are you doing?

329
00:22:00.291 --> 00:22:03.999
With this power? Anything
I damn well please.

330
00:22:04.000 --> 00:22:05.290
But I thought...

331
00:22:05.291 --> 00:22:09.124
That I wanted to save the world
from the Emergence? Please.

332
00:22:09.125 --> 00:22:13.790
I played the reluctant hero for a
hot minute to get what I needed.

333
00:22:13.791 --> 00:22:15.500
You.

334
00:22:17.083 --> 00:22:18.249
Now.

335
00:22:18.250 --> 00:22:21.124
kneel before me.

336
00:22:21.125 --> 00:22:23.582
- Yes. my queen.
- Oh. yes!

337
00:22:23.583 --> 00:22:26.207
Savin' the big twist
for the Third Act reel!

338
00:22:26.208 --> 00:22:27.665
Howard.
take it seriously.

339
00:22:27.666 --> 00:22:30.040
With her magic and now the
power of two Celestials.

340
00:22:30.041 --> 00:22:33.457
she can destroy the whole world
and remake it however she wants.

341
00:22:33.458 --> 00:22:35.499
Surely. you've worked with
difficult actors before.

342
00:22:35.500 --> 00:22:37.040
Must be a way to
get through to her.

343
00:22:37.041 --> 00:22:38.582
I mean. all actors
are difficult.

344
00:22:38.583 --> 00:22:41.875
We're all sensitive 'cause we're
opening up our souls. so the...

345
00:22:43.041 --> 00:22:44.666
Jarvis. you're a genius.

346
00:22:46.666 --> 00:22:48.166
Agatha. stop.

347
00:22:48.708 --> 00:22:51.165
I would have thought
you'd have realized by now

348
00:22:51.166 --> 00:22:54.749
I'm not an actress who
likes to take direction!

349
00:22:54.750 --> 00:22:56.625
Now. kneel before me.

350
00:22:57.208 --> 00:22:58.332
This isn't you.

351
00:22:58.333 --> 00:23:00.207
You don't know me.

352
00:23:00.208 --> 00:23:01.582
Of course. I do.

353
00:23:01.583 --> 00:23:03.249
Because you're just like me.

354
00:23:03.250 --> 00:23:05.875
and everyone else who
came to this stupid town.

355
00:23:06.625 --> 00:23:10.332
At some point. somewhere in our
lives. the world made us feel small.

356
00:23:10.333 --> 00:23:11.875
so we set out to show them.

357
00:23:12.916 --> 00:23:15.374
But. Agatha. you never
needed all this power.

358
00:23:15.375 --> 00:23:18.749
Because you've always had the only
magic you'd ever really needed

359
00:23:18.750 --> 00:23:20.082
to leave your mark on the world.

360
00:23:20.083 --> 00:23:21.999
Uh-huh. uh-huh.

361
00:23:22.000 --> 00:23:23.749
And what magic is that?

362
00:23:23.750 --> 00:23:24.833
The movies.

363
00:23:25.666 --> 00:23:28.665
The movies are magic. Agatha.

364
00:23:28.666 --> 00:23:29.999
Hell. they're better than magic.

365
00:23:30.000 --> 00:23:32.624
Because they change the
world by changing people.

366
00:23:32.625 --> 00:23:35.165
By making them feel
something real.

367
00:23:35.166 --> 00:23:38.457
And with that kind of power.
you don't have to be feared.

368
00:23:38.458 --> 00:23:41.416
Because you can be adored.

369
00:23:45.791 --> 00:23:49.833
You can't possibly understand
how long I've worked for this.

370
00:23:50.333 --> 00:23:53.458
Well. I've been on Earth for
thousands of years. so I kinda do.

371
00:23:54.375 --> 00:23:57.291
And if you're anything like
me. maybe all this time.

372
00:23:57.833 --> 00:24:00.166
you've just been looking
for the right collaborator.

373
00:24:05.916 --> 00:24:07.291
So. what do you say?

374
00:24:07.958 --> 00:24:10.833
Wanna change the
world? For real?

375
00:24:34.583 --> 00:24:36.124
Reporting
live from Hollywood.

376
00:24:36.125 --> 00:24:39.457
where there's more stars on the red
carpet than there are in the sky.

377
00:24:39.458 --> 00:24:40.540
Over here. One more!

378
00:24:40.541 --> 00:24:43.332
Mr. Stark! Mr. Stark! The
trades are predicting a blockbuster.

379
00:24:43.333 --> 00:24:44.957
What will it mean
for your weapons biz?

380
00:24:44.958 --> 00:24:48.082
Wars. my friend. are a thing of
the past. Cinema is the future.

381
00:24:51.041 --> 00:24:53.374
Kingo and I. we
wanted to make a movie

382
00:24:53.375 --> 00:24:56.291
that would. well...
change the world.

383
00:24:56.875 --> 00:24:57.874
And I think we did.

384
00:24:57.875 --> 00:25:01.290
Some sparks flew. that's for sure.

385
00:25:01.291 --> 00:25:03.082
Now. just wait for the sequel.

386
00:25:03.083 --> 00:25:05.041
- Hey. Kingo!
- Agatha!

387
00:25:08.833 --> 00:25:10.874
That sequel could come
sooner than you think.

388
00:25:10.875 --> 00:25:12.165
Since you revived them.

389
00:25:12.166 --> 00:25:14.707
Ajak and the other Eternals
are pretty concerned

390
00:25:14.708 --> 00:25:18.665
that killing Arishem has probably
drawn the Celestials' attention.

391
00:25:18.666 --> 00:25:21.582
Hah! Too bad for them.
We thrive on attention.

392
00:25:22.666 --> 00:25:24.790
Yeah. but this is the
bad kind of attention.

393
00:25:24.791 --> 00:25:26.957
Oh. darling. we can save
that for the sequel.

394
00:25:28.291 --> 00:25:32.332
Oh. my God! It
looks so gorgeous!

395
00:25:32.333 --> 00:25:34.166
This is so beautiful!

396
00:25:36.416 --> 00:25:38.457
<i>Everyone
has a story worth telling.</i>

397
00:25:38.458 --> 00:25:41.666
<i>Even two lost souls
on the wrong path.</i>

398
00:25:42.375 --> 00:25:45.958
<i>But sometimes. all it takes
is a trip to the movies</i>

399
00:25:46.500 --> 00:25:49.958
<i>to remind you that
anything is possible.</i>

400
00:25:51.041 --> 00:25:52.500
<i>Even a happy ending.</i>

401
00:25:55.291 --> 00:25:57.957
<i>Then again. who doesn't
love a cliffhanger?</i>

402
00:28:13.000 --> 00:28:14.583
<i>And cut!</i>

402
00:28:15.305 --> 00:29:15.778
Do you want subtitles for any video?
